  "prompt": "What should be my 12th board percentage to get admission in St. Xavier's College Autonomous, Mumbai for B.Com?",
  "response": "Admission to St. Xavier's College (Autonomous), Mumbai for the B.Com program is highly competitive and primarily based on **Class 12th board exam marks**. However, the exact cut-off percentage varies each year depending on factors like:\n\n1. **Number of applicants**\n2. **Difficulty level of the board exams**\n3. **Overall performance of applicants**\n\nHere's a general guideline:\n\n- **Cut-off Range**: In recent years, the cut-off for B.Com at St. Xavier's has been **90% or above** for most boards (CBSE, ISC, Maharashtra State Board, etc.).\n- **Higher Boards**: For CBSE and ISC, the cut-off is slightly higher, often **92-95% or more**.\n- **Management Quota**: For reserved or management quota seats, the cut-off may be slightly lower, but these seats are limited and highly competitive.\n\n### Tips to Improve Your Chances:\n1. **Aim for 90%+**: To be on the safer side, aim for a percentage in the **90s**.\n2. **Focus on Core Subjects**: Especially accountancy, mathematics, and economics, as these are key subjects for B.Com.\n3. **Extracurricular Activities**: While the admission is merit-based, participation in extracurricular activities can strengthen your profile for other selection criteria or interviews (if applicable).\n4. **Apply Early**: Keep an eye on the admission notification and apply as soon as the process opens.\n\n### Other Criteria:\n- **Universities/Boards Preference**: St. Xavier's gives preference to certain boards like CBSE, ISC, and Maharashtra State Board.\n- **Entrance Test (if applicable)**: Some programs may require an entrance test or interview, though B.Com admissions are primarily merit-based.\n\nFor the latest and most accurate information, check the official **St. Xavier's College website** or contact their admissions office. Cut-offs can change yearly, so it's crucial to stay updated.",
